(
  'mcq',
  'rw',
  'In a study of the mechanisms underlying associative memory-or the ability to learn and remember connections between inherently unrelated things-neuroscientists Kei Igarashi, Jasmine Chavez, and others presented mice with memory tests. The team discovered that fan cells, a type of cell found in the medial temporal lobe of the brain, are necessary for the acquisition of new associative memories. They also found that fan cell activity requires dopamine, a chemical the brain produces in response to pleasure and rewards. Consequently, receiving a reward should likely help to ______ Which choice most logically completes the text?',
