  '[{"id":"a","text":"To bring attention to overlooked African artists"},{"id":"b","text":"To teach young people why recycling is important"},{"id":"c","text":"To help adults gain important outdoor skills"},{"id":"d","text":"To give teenagers advice about starting businesses"}]'::jsonb,
  'b',
  'Choice B is the best answer because it describes a reason that Moejoh and team founded U-recycle Initiative Africa. The text mentions two reasons the initiative was founded: to teach young people about how they affect the environment and to teach them "why recycling is important." Thus, teaching the importance of recycling to young people accurately describes a motivation that the text cites as a reason for the initiative''s founding. Choice A is incorrect. Although art is mentioned in the text, there are no details about artists or whether they are being overlooked. Choice C is incorrect because the text is explicitly about young people and their relationship to the environment and recycling. There is no mention of adults or outdoor skills. Choice D is incorrect. Although the text discusses young people, which likely includes teenagers, there is no mention of starting businesses.',
